  <main class="lesson-content">
    <h2>Lesson: Introduction to Computers</h2>
    <div class="objectives">
      <h3>Lesson Objectives</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Define what a computer is.</li>
        <li>Explain basic uses of computers.</li>
        <li>Identify the main components of a computer system.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="notes">
      <h3>Lesson Notes</h3>
      <p>
        A computer is an electronic device that accepts input, processes it, stores it, and gives output.
        Computers are used in education, health, business, entertainment, and many more areas.
        The main components include:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Input Devices</strong> – e.g., keyboard, mouse.</li>
        <li><strong>Processing Unit</strong> – Central Processing Unit (CPU).</li>
        <li><strong>Storage Devices</strong> – e.g., hard disk, flash drive.</li>
        <li><strong>Output Devices</strong> – e.g., monitor, printer.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="activities">
      <h3>Class Activities</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Draw and label the basic computer components.</li>
        <li>Discuss five areas where computers are used in everyday life.</li>
        <li>Pair activity: Match components to their functions.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

